lPermission` with `ActionSettingsRead`/`ActionSettingsWrite` and `ScopeSettingsOAuth` scope\n\nThe Social/OAuth provider layer in `pkg/login/social/` manages authentication clients:\n- `social.go` defines the `Service` interface and `SocialConnector` interface with `OAuthInfo` configuration\n- `socialimpl/service.go` implements `SocialService` with `ProvideService` that initializes OAuth connectors by loading SSO settings from the database\n- OAuth connector implementations in `connectors/` (generic_oauth.go, github_oauth.go, gitlab_oauth.go, google_oauth.go, azuread_oauth.go, okta_oauth.go, grafana_com_oauth.go) all implement the `Reloadable` interface and call `ssoSettings.RegisterReloadable()` to register themselves for dynamic configuration updates\n- The connectors receive `OAuthInfo` from SSO settings and use it to configure their OAuth flow parameters\n\n**Layer 4: Access Control and DI Registration**\nAccess control is defined in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/`:\n- `models.go` defines `ActionSettingsRead` and `ActionSettingsWrite` actions, and the `ScopeSettingsOAuth` function that generates provider-specific scopes\n- `ssoutils/utils.go` contains evaluators: `EvalAuthenticationSettings` for SAML/LDAP and `OauthSettingsEvaluator` for OAuth providers\n- `roles.go` defines role-based access control configurations\n\nDependency injection is wired in `pkg/server/wire.go`:\n- Line 426-427: `ssoSettingsImpl.ProvideService` is called and bound to `ssosettings.Service` interface\n- This ensures the SSO settings service, API endpoints, and all reloadable providers are properly initialized and registered with access control middleware\n\nThe flow: `ProvideService` (service.go) → creates `Api` via `ProvideApi` → calls `RegisterAPIEndpoints` → wires with `SocialService` which registers all OAuth connectors as `Reloadable` implementations → access control evaluators protect the endpoints"
