  "text": "The SSO Settings control in Grafana spans across 4 critical layers:\n\n**Layer 1: Feature Flag Definition**\nThe feature flag for SSO Settings is defined in `pkg/services/featuremgmt/registry.go` at line 1039-1046 as `ssoSettingsLDAP`, which enables the new SSO Settings API for LDAP configuration. The generated constant `FlagSsoSettingsLDAP` is located in `pkg/services/featuremgmt/toggles_gen.go` at line 556 and is used throughout the codebase to conditionally enable SSO settings features.\n\n**Layer 2: SSO Settings Infrastructure**\nThe core infrastructure is defined in `pkg/services/ssosettings/` directory:\n- `ssosettings.go` defines three key interfaces: `Service` (for SSO settings operations), `Reloadable` (for provider reload/validation), `FallbackStrategy` (for configuration loading), and `Store` (for database operations)\n- `models/models.go` contains the `SSOSettings` data model and `SettingsSource` enum\n- `database/database.go` implements `SSOSettingsStore` with the `ProvideStore` function for database operations\n- `ssosettingsimpl/service.go` contains the `Service` struct and `ProvideService` function that wires together all dependencies including the database store, feature toggles, secrets service, and API registration\n- Error definitions are in `errors.go`\n- Fallback strategies are implemented in `strategies/` (oauth_strategy.go, ldap_strategy.go, saml_strategy.go) to load settings from configuration files\n- Validation logic is in `validation/` with OAuth-specific validators\n- Migrations are defined in `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ssosettings/migrations.go`\n\n**Layer 3: API and Authentication Wiring**\nThe REST API layer is implemented in `pkg/services/ssosettings/api/api.go`:\n- The `Api` struct is initialized via `ProvideApi` function\n- `RegisterAPIEndpoints` registers four endpoints: GET/PUT/DELETE for provider settings and GET for listing all settings\n- Each endpoint is protected with access control middleware using `ac.EvalPermission` with `ActionSettingsRead`/`ActionSettingsWrite` and `ScopeSettingsOAuth` scope\n\nThe Social/OAuth provider layer in `pkg/login/social/` manages authentication clients:\n- `social.go` defines the `Service` interface and `SocialConnector` interface with `OAuthInfo` configuration\n- `socialimpl/service.go` implements `SocialService` with `ProvideService` that initializes OAuth connectors by loading SSO settings from the database\n- OAuth connector implementations in `connectors/` (generic_oauth.go, github_oauth.go, gitlab_oauth.go, google_oauth.go, azuread_oauth.go, okta_oauth.go, grafana_com_oauth.go) all implement the `Reloadable` interface and call `ssoSettings.RegisterReloadable()` to register themselves for dynamic configuration updates\n- The connectors receive `OAuthInfo` from SSO settings and use it to configure their OAuth flow parameters\n\n**Layer 4: Access Control and DI Registration**\nAccess control is defined in `pkg/services/accesscontrol/`:\n- `models.go` defines `ActionSettingsRead` and `ActionSettingsWrite` actions, and the `ScopeSettingsOAuth` function that generates provider-specific scopes\n- `ssoutils/utils.go` contains evaluators: `EvalAuthenticationSettings` for SAML/LDAP and `OauthSettingsEvaluator` for OAuth providers\n- `roles.go` defines role-based access control configurations\n\nDependency injection is wired in `pkg/server/wire.go`:\n- Line 426-427: `ssoSettingsImpl.ProvideService` is called and bound to `ssosettings.Service` interface\n- This ensures the SSO settings service, API endpoints, and all reloadable providers are properly initialized and registered with access control middleware\n\nThe flow: `ProvideService` (service.go) → creates `Api` via `ProvideApi` → calls `RegisterAPIEndpoints` → wires with `SocialService` which registers all OAuth connectors as `Reloadable` implementations → access control evaluators protect the endpoints"
